		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message28853523">Plot holes usually don't bother me if the show "doesn't take itself seriously", is "over the top", or runs on cartoon logic like Kill la Kill. In some series such as Code Geass, it was so wildly enjoyable that I didn't care about plot holes or it making complete sense. Now that show was entertainment at its finest! However, the more serious a show takes itself, the more I am bothered by plot holes. If a show is dead serious like most Gundam in the Universal Century then mishaps don't fly. <br />
<br />
Recently a show that bothered me was The Eccentric Family. The professor said something close to, "I love animals so I want to eat them." I thought, "What kind of logic is that!" Another show was Shiki, where it took the majority of the characters more than half the series to begin to warm up to the notion that something may be awry in their town. </div><div style="margin-top: 8px;"><em>Modified by Nagisa33, 02-21-14, 7:26 PM</em></div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
